plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Arial'  #   'Cairo'  'Tahoma'

#        
def fix_arabic_text(text):
    reshaped_text = arabic_reshaper.reshape(text)  #   
    bidi_text = get_display(reshaped_text)  #     
    return bidi_text

#     
country_stats = df.groupby("Country")["AverageTemperature"].agg(["mean", "median", "max", "min", "std"]).reset_index()

#         
country_stats["Country"] = country_stats["Country"].apply(fix_arabic_text)

#  10  
top_10_hottest = country_stats.nlargest(10, "mean")

#  10  
top_10_coldest = country_stats.nsmallest(10, "mean")

#      10  
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 6))

#    10  
sns.barplot(x="mean", y="Country", hue="Country", data=top_10_hottest, palette="Reds", ax=ax[0], legend=False)
ax[0].set_title(fix_arabic_text("  10    "), fontsize=14)
ax[0].set_xlabel(fix_arabic_text("   (C)"), fontsize=12)
ax[0].set_ylabel(fix_arabic_text(""), fontsize=12)
ax[0].invert_yaxis()  #      

#    
for i, v in enumerate(top_10_hottest["mean"]):
    ax[0].text(v + 0.2, i, f"{v:.1f}C", color="black", fontsize=10, va="center")

#    10  
sns.barplot(x="mean", y="Country", hue="Country", data=top_10_coldest, palette="Blues", ax=ax[1], legend=False)
ax[1].set_title(fix_arabic_text("  10    "), fontsize=14)
ax[1].set_xlabel(fix_arabic_text("   (C)"), fontsize=12)
ax[1].set_ylabel(fix_arabic_text(""), fontsize=12)
ax[1].invert_yaxis()  #      

#    
for i, v in enumerate(top_10_coldest["mean"]):
    ax[1].text(v + 0.2, i, f"{v:.1f}C", color="black", fontsize=10, va="center")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import arabic_reshaper
from bidi.algorithm import get_display

#     
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Arial'  #   'Cairo'  'Tahoma'

#       
def fix_arabic_text(text):
    reshaped_text = arabic_reshaper.reshape(text)  #   
    bidi_text = get_display(reshaped_text)  #     
    return bidi_text

#     
yemen_df = df[df["Country"] == "Yemen"].copy()

#     'dt'  
yemen_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(yemen_df["dt"])

#     'dt'   
yemen_df["Month"] = yemen_df["dt"].dt.month

#      
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 4, figsize=(15, 10), sharex=True, sharey=True)
axes = axes.flatten()

#      
for i, month in enumerate(range(1, 13)):
    subset = yemen_df[yemen_df["Month"] == month]
    axes[i].hist(subset["AverageTemperature"], bins=30, color="teal", alpha=0.7, density=True)
    axes[i].set_title(fix_arabic_text(f" {month}"))  #   
    axes[i].grid(True)

#    
plt.suptitle(fix_arabic_text("        "), fontsize=16)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Arial'

def fix_arabic_text(text):
    reshaped_text = arabic_reshaper.reshape(text)
    bidi_text = get_display(reshaped_text)
    return bidi_text

#      
yemen_df["dt"] = pd.to_datetime(yemen_df["dt"])
yemen_ts = yemen_df.set_index("dt")["AverageTemperature"].dropna().asfreq("MS")

#    ARIMA
arima_model = ARIMA(yemen_ts, order=(1, 1, 1))
arima_fit = arima_model.fit()

#       2050
n_steps = (2050 - yemen_ts.index[-1].year) * 12  #    2050
forecast_mean = arima_fit.forecast(steps=n_steps)

#     
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=yemen_ts.index[-1], periods=n_steps, freq="MS")

#      
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.plot(yemen_ts, label=fix_arabic_text(" "), color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast_mean, label=fix_arabic_text(" "), color="red")

plt.title(fix_arabic_text("       2050  ARIMA"))
plt.xlabel(fix_arabic_text(""))
plt.ylabel(fix_arabic_text("   (C)"))
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import arabic_reshaper
from bidi.algorithm import get_display
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.statespace.sarimax import SARIMAX

#     
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Arial'

#       
def fix_arabic_text(text):
    reshaped_text = arabic_reshaper.reshape(text)
    bidi_text = get_display(reshaped_text)
    return bidi_text

#      
if 'yemen_ts' not in globals():
    raise ValueError("      .     .")

#    ARIMA       
arima_model = ARIMA(yemen_ts, order=(1, 1, 1)).fit()
arima_forecast = arima_model.get_forecast(steps=240)  #    2040 (240 )
forecast_mean = arima_forecast.predicted_mean  #   

#    SARIMA       
sarima_model = SARIMAX(yemen_ts, order=(1, 1, 1), seasonal_order=(1, 1, 1, 12)).fit()
sarima_forecast = sarima_model.get_forecast(steps=240)
sarima_forecast_mean = sarima_forecast.predicted_mean

#      
last_date = yemen_ts.index[-1]  #     
forecast_steps = len(forecast_mean)  #   
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=last_date, periods=forecast_steps, freq="MS")
sarima_forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=last_date, periods=len(sarima_forecast_mean), freq="MS")

#      ARIMA  SARIMA
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.plot(yemen_ts, label=fix_arabic_text(" "), color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, forecast_mean, label=fix_arabic_text("  (ARIMA)"), color="red", linestyle="dashed")
plt.plot(sarima_forecast_index, sarima_forecast_mean, label=fix_arabic_text("  (SARIMA)"), color="green", linestyle="dashed")

plt.title(fix_arabic_text("  ARIMA  SARIMA      2040"))
plt.xlabel(fix_arabic_text(""))
plt.ylabel(fix_arabic_text("   (C)"))
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
